    <h3>Consultation with your doctor </h3>
    <p>Prior to any treatment, you should visit a qualified practitioner. They will examine your skin and medical history to determine if laser hair treatment is suitable for you.</p>
    <h3>Pre-treatment planning</h3> 
    <p>The area to be treated needs to be shaved before the laser service, this helps the laser focus on the hair follicles rather than the hair on the surface.</p>
    <h3>Eye Protection</h3> 
    <p>To shield your eyes from the laser's light, you'll be provided with special goggles to wear during the procedure.</p>
    <h3>During application</h3> 
    <p>The practitioner will use a handheld device that emits the laser beams over the treatment area. You may feel mild heat / tingling sensation as the laser targets the hair follicles.</p>
