    <p>Some laser devices use cooling systems to minimize discomfort and protect the surrounding skin during the treatment.</p>
    <h3>Post-Treatment</h3> 
    <p>After the session, the practitioner may apply a soothing gel or lotion to ease any redness or irritation.</p>
    <h3>Multiple Sessions</h3> 
    <p>To achieve optimal results, it takes multiple sessions throughout the course of many weeks. The reason for this is that the hair grows in cycles, and the laser only targets hair in its active growth phase.</p>
    <h3>Follow-up and Maintenance</h3> 
    <p>After you’re done with the procedure, periodic touch-ups may be necessary to maintain the results over time.</p>
